<p>California governor Gavin Newsom said he is seriously weighing a run for the 2028 US presidency in an interview aired Sunday, and that he will make a decision after the 2026 midterm elections . Newsom has raised his national profile this year as a prominent critic of President Trump and by taking steps that observers say test the waters for a potential campaign . His announcement adds an early high-profile name to a developing field that Democrats and Republicans are already watching closely .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/xeNaQ73Y6keDbjCobkDiSGnyys_wISAo0FlOurf4nUEsRn6HjvcriBVLbA3m0XSoVmRwP0Ag0zlC1wHEsDklmzZSEj7AQUZFHa8dUlnv2o9I' alt='California Governor Gavin Newsom attends a press conference about new legislation aimed at improving nutrition in schools at Belvedere Middle School in Los Angeles, Oct. 8, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Exploratory steps: Newsom has made moves this year to test his national appeal and raise his profile ahead of any formal campaign decision .</li><li>Party competition: Former vice-president Kamala Harris publicly said she was considering a 2028 run a day before Newsom&#x27;s comments, signaling early jockeying within the Democratic field .</li><li>Policy contrast: Observers note Newsom has clashed with President Trump on immigration, National Guard deployments and redistricting, areas likely to shape his campaign message .</li><li>Legal context: Under the US Constitution a president cannot serve more than two terms, a restriction media note when discussing President Trump&#x27;s public comments about staying in office .</li></ul><blockquote>Iâ€™m looking forward to who presents themselves in 2028 and who meets that moment, - Gavin Newsom</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Gavin Newsom: Newsom said he is considering a 2028 presidential run and will decide after the 2026 midterm elections . (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1951500/california-governor-mulls-2028-us-presidential-run'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>Kam